title.tictactoe: Tic-tac-toe, also known as crosses or Xs and Os is a game for two players, X and O, who take turns marking the spaces in a 3Ã—3 grid. The player who succeeds in placing three of their marks in a horizontal, vertical, or diagonal row is the winner.
title._2048: 2048 is a pair up game with 2 and its exponential multiple where adjacent numbers in the same row or column merge into one i.e. add if the they are same. With each slide or arrow triggered, 2 or 4 is generated at a random cell / block.
title.pairup: Pairup is a board game played on 3X3 grid by a single player. The target for this game is to form a number from the preloaded/initial numbers 1 to 9
